issue.title: Coulomb friction parameters not handled properly in dart

content.raw: I just looked at the dart source code, and it looks like [it is using a friction pyramid internally](https://github.com/dartsim/dart/blob/v4.2.1/dart/constraint/ContactConstraint.cpp#L184-L222), so this is probably the right set of parameters.
content.html: I just looked at the dart source code, and it looks like it is using a friction pyramid internally, so this is probably the right set of parameters.

issue.title: Coulomb friction parameters not handled properly in dart

content.raw:
Yes, it's using a friction pyramid internally but uses single friction coefficient for the two friction directions by [taking the lower single friction coefficient of the colliding bodies](https://github.com/dartsim/dart/blob/master/dart/constraint/ContactConstraint.cpp#L114-115).

Supporting two friction coefficient with custom friction direction will be implemented in the future.

issue.title: Coulomb friction parameters not handled properly in dart

content.raw:
pull request #1386 provides support for setting a single friction coefficient, though custom friction directions with separate friction coefficients are not yet supported.

see the following upstream issues:

* https://github.com/dartsim/dart/issues/141
* https://github.com/dartsim/dart/issues/200
